        <briefdescription>
<para>Defines how an entity responds to a collision event. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="namespacehelios_1_1engine_1_1modules_1_1physics_1_1collision_1_1types_1a3c17ab6bf5f5cf9dc514ff7c5bf91bdc" kindref="member">CollisionBehavior</ref> values are used as bitmasks to configure per-layer collision responses in CollisionComponent. Multiple behaviors can be combined using bitwise operations.</para>
<para>The behavior determines what action the collision system takes when two entities collide based on their layer configuration.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Not all behaviors are currently fully implemented. Currently supported:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>`Reflect` - Fully supported</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>`Bounce` - Fully supported</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>`Despawn` - Fully supported </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
